    "title": "了 (le) — change of state",
    "explanation": "了 (le) at the end of a sentence indicates a change of state or new situation. 下雨了 = 'it has started raining / it is now raining'. 来了 = 'has come / is here now'. This is one of the most frequently used particles in Chinese.",
